3
00:00:22.272 --> 00:00:24.066
[electronic chiming]

4
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.490
[music stops]

5
00:00:46.255 --> 00:00:47.840
[chiming continues]

6
00:00:51.426 --> 00:00:52.427
Fine.

7
00:00:53.303 --> 00:00:54.304
Fine.

8
00:00:57.224 --> 00:00:58.433
Huh.

9
00:01:10.779 --> 00:01:11.780
[grunts]

10
00:01:23.542 --> 00:01:25.002
What the hell?

11
00:01:35.179 --> 00:01:37.597
[beeping]

12
00:01:37.598 --> 00:01:39.766
[breathing heavily]

13
00:01:45.606 --> 00:01:47.356
[breathes shakily] Hi.

14
00:01:47.357 --> 00:01:48.482
Uh. it's Barnes.

15
00:01:48.483 --> 00:01:50.944
I'm... I'm getting a really
weird reading out here and...

16
00:01:51.695 --> 00:01:52.696
Barnes.

17
00:01:53.447 --> 00:01:55.823
Outpost 47. Yeah.

18
00:01:55.824 --> 00:01:58.619
I need to speak to Assistant
Director Verdugo...

19
00:02:00.287 --> 00:02:01.872
Yeah. I'll hold.

20
00:02:03.415 --> 00:02:05.584
- [breathes shakily]
- [beeping continues]

21
00:02:10.172 --> 00:02:11.632
[growling]

22
00:02:15.427 --> 00:02:16.470
Du-Ho.

23
00:02:18.013 --> 00:02:19.133
- [Lee] Down!
- [Cate grunts]

24
00:02:21.016 --> 00:02:22.017
Kentaro!

25
00:02:24.311 --> 00:02:25.937
Kentaro. run!

26
00:02:25.938 --> 00:02:27.397
- Come on. Move on.
- Run!

27
00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:31.443
Let's go. Come on.

28
00:02:32.528 --> 00:02:33.529
[roars]

29
00:02:39.076 --> 00:02:40.077
[in Japanese] Shit.

30
00:02:47.501 --> 00:02:48.919
[growling]

31
00:04:21.970 --> 00:04:23.639
[both grunting]

32
00:04:24.765 --> 00:04:26.641
- [in English] Nice shooting. Tex.
- At least I tried.

33
00:04:26.642 --> 00:04:29.352
- You could've gotten killed. you idiot.
- Quiet.

34
00:04:29.353 --> 00:04:30.938
[footsteps thudding]

35
00:04:35.692 --> 00:04:38.069
[creature growling]

36
00:04:38.070 --> 00:04:40.030
- [thudding continues]
- [rumbling]

37
00:04:58.131 --> 00:04:59.633
[growling continues]

38
00:05:02.177 --> 00:05:03.762
[May groaning. shivers]

39
00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:08.558
[gasps. groans]

40
00:05:08.559 --> 00:05:10.769
[creature growls]

41
00:05:11.895 --> 00:05:13.397
[May whimpering]

42
00:05:17.693 --> 00:05:19.194
[breathing shakily. groaning]

43
00:05:28.912 --> 00:05:29.996
[footsteps departing]

44
00:05:29.997 --> 00:05:32.373
- [Kentaro whispering] What do we do now?
- [breathes shakily]

45
00:05:32.374 --> 00:05:33.833
We can't fight it.

46
00:05:33.834 --> 00:05:35.252
I wouldn't recommend it.

47
00:05:49.641 --> 00:05:51.225
I think we're in the
clear for the moment.

48
00:05:51.226 --> 00:05:52.310
[May gasps. groans]

49
00:05:52.311 --> 00:05:54.854
- Goddamn it! Son of a bitch!
- No. no. no. no. no. [shushes]

50
00:05:54.855 --> 00:05:58.941
[panting] My legs
are soaking wet.

51
00:05:58.942 --> 00:06:01.570
[shushes] Then we
gotta move quick.

52
00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:04.156
[May whimpers]

53
00:06:04.157 --> 00:06:06.073
[Kentaro] Come on. May.
Get up. Get up. get up.

54
00:06:06.074 --> 00:06:07.742
- Come on. May. you good?
- [groaning]

55
00:06:07.743 --> 00:06:09.952
[May] Am I good? I'm
gonna die of hypothermia.

56
00:06:09.953 --> 00:06:11.370
Are you happy we came?

57
00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:13.040
[breathing heavily]

58
00:06:19.421 --> 00:06:21.461
[person. in Japanese] Your
work is a bold statement.

59
00:06:21.673 --> 00:06:22.840
Why this?

60
00:06:22.841 --> 00:06:24.092
Why now?

61
00:06:25.552 --> 00:06:26.637
Uh...

62
00:06:28.055 --> 00:06:29.056
[person] House lights!

63
00:06:31.099 --> 00:06:32.099
You hesitated.

64
00:06:33.727 --> 00:06:34.853
It's a complicated question.

65
00:06:35.812 --> 00:06:38.649
And you've had months to
come up with an answer.

66
00:06:38.857 --> 00:06:39.857
Art...

67
00:06:40.442 --> 00:06:43.736
comes from a place you don't
feel comfortable talking about.

68
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:45.113
To me it's just intuitive.

69
00:06:46.573 --> 00:06:48.450
I respect your process.

70
00:06:49.201 --> 00:06:52.620
But if buyers are going to
plunk down money. good money.

71
00:06:52.621 --> 00:06:56.416
they want to know what they are
getting. Who they are getting.

72
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:58.125
People...

73
00:06:58.126 --> 00:06:59.168
don't buy the art...

74
00:06:59.169 --> 00:07:00.671
they buy the artist.

75
00:07:01.839 --> 00:07:03.047
I know. Kimi.

76
00:07:03.048 --> 00:07:03.966
I'm sorry.

77
00:07:03.967 --> 00:07:05.550
You have two hours
before we open the doors

78
00:07:05.551 --> 00:07:07.760
to figure out an answer
that makes me believe you.

79
00:07:07.761 --> 00:07:10.639
We both have a lot
at stake tonight.

80
00:07:13.517 --> 00:07:15.227
[Kimi. speaking Japanese]

81
00:07:16.061 --> 00:07:17.062
[Kentaro] Hey. Mom.

82
00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:22.441
"Kentaro Randa's assertive
exploration of parallels and interiors

83
00:07:22.442 --> 00:07:27.573
invites the viewer to challenge
their assumptions about identity."

84
00:07:29.032 --> 00:07:32.244
Who knew my son
was so provocative?

85
00:07:32.870 --> 00:07:34.162
I'm not.

86
00:07:35.789 --> 00:07:37.331
Everyone's going to love it.

87
00:07:37.332 --> 00:07:41.295
It wouldn't be very "provocative"
if everyone loved it.

88
00:07:43.130 --> 00:07:44.298
[sighs]

89
00:07:45.549 --> 00:07:46.550
Hey...

90
00:07:47.009 --> 00:07:48.302
I'm proud of you.

91
00:07:49.344 --> 00:07:50.804
So is your father.

92
00:07:52.389 --> 00:07:53.765
He hasn't even seen it.

93
00:07:54.266 --> 00:07:56.268
He will tonight.

94
00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:59.062
He's coming straight from
the airport. [chuckles]

95
00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:04.234
I'm going to get some air...

96
00:08:06.111 --> 00:08:10.032
before everyone wants to meet
the "provocative" new artist.

97
00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:14.702
Kentaro...

98
00:08:14.703 --> 00:08:16.495
you've worked hard for this.

99
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:17.748
You deserve it.

100
00:08:21.293 --> 00:08:22.294
There are snacks.

101
00:08:23.086 --> 00:08:24.421
[Emiko. in English] Mmm.

102
00:08:33.639 --> 00:08:35.319
[in Japanese] Did you
just take my picture?

103
00:08:35.682 --> 00:08:36.682
No.

104
00:08:38.519 --> 00:08:39.810
[in English] Bullshit.

105
00:08:39.811 --> 00:08:40.978
[in Japanese] I saw you.

106
00:08:40.979 --> 00:08:42.812
[Kentaro] I was taking a picture
of my poster for my show.

107
00:08:42.813 --> 00:08:46.193
and you walked in front of
it gawking like a tourist.

108
00:08:50.113 --> 00:08:53.115
[in English] "Parallels and
Interiors." Sounds pretentious.

109
00:08:53.116 --> 00:08:54.368
Incredibly.

110
00:09:01.124 --> 00:09:04.795
You know what would be incredibly
respectful is if you...

111
00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:11.093
Yeah.

112
00:09:12.135 --> 00:09:14.096
- Deleted.
- Thank you.

113
00:09:16.932 --> 00:09:19.226
Is there a reason you don't
like your picture being taken?

114
00:09:22.521 --> 00:09:23.522
I...

115
00:09:24.022 --> 00:09:25.607
It's a very nice picture.

116
00:09:30.571 --> 00:09:31.697
Are you hitting on me?

117
00:09:32.990 --> 00:09:34.199
Just being honest.

118
00:09:38.912 --> 00:09:40.247
Is this really you?

119
00:09:41.957 --> 00:09:42.957
Yeah.

120
00:09:42.958 --> 00:09:44.543
Is there wine?

121
00:09:47.462 --> 00:09:50.590
It's cheap. Bad. Pretentious.

122
00:09:50.591 --> 00:09:52.091
[chuckles]

123
00:09:52.092 --> 00:09:53.259
Pretentious wine.

124
00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:54.635
Right.

125
00:09:54.636 --> 00:09:55.928
Do you like whiskey?

126
00:09:55.929 --> 00:09:58.222
I like expensive whiskey.

127
00:09:58.223 --> 00:10:00.934
You're in luck. Japan has
some very expensive whiskey.

128
00:10:02.644 --> 00:10:03.728
Cool.

129
00:10:03.729 --> 00:10:05.438
- I know a place.
- Now?

130
00:10:05.439 --> 00:10:07.191
But don't you have a show?

131
00:10:08.692 --> 00:10:10.777
Um. I'll make an entrance later.

132
00:10:11.528 --> 00:10:12.653
Oh.

133
00:10:12.654 --> 00:10:14.114
[chuckles] Okay.

134
00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:15.740
I'm Kentaro.

135
00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:18.160
I'm May.

136
00:10:18.869 --> 00:10:19.870
May.

137
00:10:20.370 --> 00:10:22.705
[Kentaro] May. May. Where
are you going? Slow down.

138
00:10:22.706 --> 00:10:24.124
Slow down? [pants]

139
00:10:24.833 --> 00:10:27.668
Unless you want to add a set of
toes to what you already owe me.

140
00:10:27.669 --> 00:10:28.794
you need to speed your ass up.

141
00:10:28.795 --> 00:10:30.796
He's right. May.
Conserve your energy.

142
00:10:30.797 --> 00:10:32.882
Wet legs. you're gonna
be fighting hypothermia.

143
00:10:32.883 --> 00:10:34.050
[Kentaro] We gotta get you dry.

144
00:10:34.051 --> 00:10:37.553
No. Even if there was anything
out here to build a fire with.

145
00:10:37.554 --> 00:10:40.015
we can't sit still with
that Titan on the prowl.

146
00:10:40.891 --> 00:10:43.226
- You still think it's out there?
- [Lee] Hell if I know.

147
00:10:43.227 --> 00:10:46.479
[May] What are you ta... What happened
to your centuries of experience now. huh?

148
00:10:46.480 --> 00:10:47.940
It's a Titan. May.

149
00:10:48.649 --> 00:10:50.067
They're like snowflakes.

150
00:10:50.776 --> 00:10:52.735
Never came across
two that were same.

151
00:10:52.736 --> 00:10:56.656
Okay. Well. maybe there's some info
on these precious files of yours.

152
00:10:56.657 --> 00:10:57.740
Go to hell

153
00:10:57.741 --> 00:11:00.785
- and take your life's work with you.
- Hey. Easy with these. Now come on. May.

154
00:11:00.786 --> 00:11:01.994
[Cate] Once the sun goes down.

155
00:11:01.995 --> 00:11:03.663
the temperature's gonna
drop by the minute.

156
00:11:03.664 --> 00:11:05.456
We've got no food. no shelter.

157
00:11:05.457 --> 00:11:06.958
No Du-Ho.

158
00:11:06.959 --> 00:11:08.626
[sighs] Where the
hell are we going?

159
00:11:08.627 --> 00:11:10.795
Northwest. We head
for the coast.

160
00:11:10.796 --> 00:11:13.172
Greater probability of
running into people there.

161
00:11:13.173 --> 00:11:14.257
[sighs]

162
00:11:14.258 --> 00:11:16.259
- I think I saw something from the plane.
- [Lee] What?

163
00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:18.177
[stammers] Saw what?

164
00:11:18.178 --> 00:11:21.138
Some kind of structure.
Looked like a big golf ball.

165
00:11:21.139 --> 00:11:22.223
[Lee scoffs]

166
00:11:22.224 --> 00:11:24.601
It had to be man-made. like
a building or settlement.

167
00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:26.477
All right. All right.

168
00:11:26.478 --> 00:11:28.062
Did either one of you see it?

169
00:11:28.063 --> 00:11:29.147
No.

170
00:11:31.483 --> 00:11:32.734
But May did.

171
00:11:33.277 --> 00:11:34.527
What? No.

172
00:11:34.528 --> 00:11:36.779
No. You said you saw something.

173
00:11:36.780 --> 00:11:37.865
I didn't see anything.

174
00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:40.050
[in Japanese] You're
taking their side?

175
00:11:40.534 --> 00:11:42.034
[in English] Is it 'cause
you're pissed at me?

176
00:11:42.035 --> 00:11:44.996
No. This has nothing to do with you.
This is about me freezing to death.

177
00:11:44.997 --> 00:11:46.622
I'm trying to save
you. Will you just...

178
00:11:46.623 --> 00:11:47.708
Trust me.

179
00:11:56.925 --> 00:11:58.718
- [knocks]
- [Kentaro. in Japanese] Sota?

180
00:11:58.719 --> 00:11:59.678
[Sota] <i>Password.</i>

181
00:11:59.679 --> 00:12:01.345
Sota. It's me. man. Kentaro.

182
00:12:01.346 --> 00:12:02.471
[Sota] <i>Who?</i>

183
00:12:02.472 --> 00:12:03.557
Kentaro.

184
00:12:03.932 --> 00:12:05.350
- [Sota] <i>Password.</i>
- [static]

185
00:12:06.059 --> 00:12:09.270
[in English] Okay. Forget
about it. This place is a dump.

186
00:12:09.271 --> 00:12:10.271
[in Japanese] Dump!

187
00:12:11.940 --> 00:12:12.941
[Sota] Hurry up!

188
00:12:17.571 --> 00:12:19.406
[door buzzing]

189
00:12:21.033 --> 00:12:22.783
Dump?!

190
00:12:22.784 --> 00:12:24.118
She didn't mean it.

191
00:12:24.119 --> 00:12:25.828
[chuckles] Prove me wrong.

192
00:12:25.829 --> 00:12:27.413
[chuckles]

193
00:12:27.414 --> 00:12:28.624
[in English] I like you.

194
00:12:29.208 --> 00:12:31.126
[in Japanese] And you're
too easy to mess with.

195
00:12:35.255 --> 00:12:37.508
[in English] Okay.
You've proved me wrong.

196
00:12:38.509 --> 00:12:39.789
[in Japanese] May. this is Sota.

197
00:12:40.219 --> 00:12:41.053
Owner.

198
00:12:41.053 --> 00:12:41.970
Manager.

199
00:12:41.971 --> 00:12:43.012
Asshole.

200
00:12:43.013 --> 00:12:44.640
[chuckles] Guilty
of all charges.

201
00:12:45.849 --> 00:12:47.976
[in English] Wait. You
have your own bottle?

202
00:12:48.894 --> 00:12:50.478
You are as pretentious
as I thought.

203
00:12:50.479 --> 00:12:51.562
That's how it works here.

204
00:12:51.563 --> 00:12:52.814
Uh-huh.

205
00:12:53.732 --> 00:12:56.493
- [in Japanese] But maybe we can do better.
- [Sota. in English] Okay.

206
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:01.739
Oh. Okay.

207
00:13:01.740 --> 00:13:03.241
So. you're a successful artist.

208
00:13:03.242 --> 00:13:04.367
I designed the lighting here.

209
00:13:04.368 --> 00:13:05.327
[glasses clinking]

210
00:13:05.328 --> 00:13:07.453
- What? No way.
- Yeah.

211
00:13:07.454 --> 00:13:08.372
Oh.

212
00:13:08.373 --> 00:13:11.083
So. he lets me pretend.
and even open early for me.

213
00:13:12.376 --> 00:13:13.544
[speaks Japanese]

214
00:13:19.716 --> 00:13:20.717
What do you do?

215
00:13:21.218 --> 00:13:22.845
Uh. computer shit.

216
00:13:23.345 --> 00:13:27.390
It's not nearly as interesting as
art. How long have you been doing it?

217
00:13:27.391 --> 00:13:28.474
Since I was little.

218
00:13:28.475 --> 00:13:30.643
But as a job. I
guess. since tonight.

219
00:13:30.644 --> 00:13:33.187
What? Like... What do
you mean? [chuckles]

220
00:13:33.188 --> 00:13:35.065
- Like. tonight's your first show?
- Yeah.

221
00:13:36.275 --> 00:13:38.192
Don't you feel like
you should be there?

222
00:13:38.193 --> 00:13:40.237
Um. I'm letting
the suspense build.

223
00:13:40.988 --> 00:13:43.739
- It's all part of the act.
- Oh. Part of the act.

224
00:13:43.740 --> 00:13:45.074
Is this part of the act?

225
00:13:45.075 --> 00:13:46.450
W-What do you mean?

226
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:50.122
The secret whiskey bar and you.
the artist. next big thing.

227
00:13:51.540 --> 00:13:53.040
[in Japanese] Does
he bring other girls?

228
00:13:53.041 --> 00:13:55.501
As a bartender. I can't say.

229
00:13:55.502 --> 00:13:57.378
- [chuckles]
- [chuckles] Asshole.

230
00:13:57.379 --> 00:13:59.589
[in English] I mean. I
didn't say it was a bad act.

231
00:13:59.590 --> 00:14:01.091
I mean. as far as acts go.

232
00:14:03.051 --> 00:14:04.219
This isn't an act.

233
00:14:06.805 --> 00:14:10.808
I judge an artist based on their
art. not on a suit and a haircut.

234
00:14:10.809 --> 00:14:12.394
- [lock clicking]
- [keys jingle]

235
00:14:18.358 --> 00:14:19.443
[door closes]

236
00:14:24.156 --> 00:14:25.157
What?

237
00:14:25.657 --> 00:14:27.534
Why isn't this stuff
in the gallery?

238
00:14:28.076 --> 00:14:29.703
[Kentaro] These aren't for sale.

239
00:14:31.496 --> 00:14:32.497
[May sighs]

240
00:14:33.248 --> 00:14:35.375
You're definitely more
than just a haircut.

241
00:14:37.294 --> 00:14:38.712
Kimi sent me to her stylist.

242
00:14:39.671 --> 00:14:40.964
People buy the artist.

243
00:14:42.633 --> 00:14:44.718
I mean. sure.

244
00:14:45.677 --> 00:14:49.056
Rich pricks who have more
money than good taste.

245
00:14:51.308 --> 00:14:54.144
Why don't you tell Kimi what
pieces you want in the show?

246
00:14:55.062 --> 00:14:56.063
[Kentaro] Hmm.

247
00:14:56.939 --> 00:14:57.981
It's her gallery.

248
00:14:58.815 --> 00:15:01.527
- She was taking a chance on me...
- Chance on you?

249
00:15:02.945 --> 00:15:04.655
Like. out of the
goodness of her heart?

250
00:15:05.739 --> 00:15:07.199
Come on. That's bullshit.

251
00:15:07.741 --> 00:15:11.411
People don't give other people a shot
unless there's something in it for them.

252
00:15:13.413 --> 00:15:14.540
That's pretty cynical.

253
00:15:16.250 --> 00:15:17.251
That's life.

254
00:15:18.502 --> 00:15:19.753
[cell phone chimes]

255
00:15:25.425 --> 00:15:26.676
You should probably go.

256
00:15:26.677 --> 00:15:29.763
The. um... The rich
pricks are waiting.

257
00:15:36.270 --> 00:15:37.271
Come with me.

258
00:15:38.772 --> 00:15:40.147
Not really my crowd.

259
00:15:40.148 --> 00:15:41.233
Mine either.

260
00:15:41.733 --> 00:15:43.986
[chuckles] Get used
to it. hotshot.

261
00:15:47.573 --> 00:15:49.241
Wait. [grunts]

262
00:15:53.662 --> 00:15:54.663
Okay.

263
00:15:55.372 --> 00:15:56.372
Now you can go.

264
00:15:56.373 --> 00:15:57.833
- [scoffs]
- [chuckles]

265
00:16:17.227 --> 00:16:18.561
[Cate sighs] Okay.

266
00:16:18.562 --> 00:16:19.980
Somebody has to say it.

267
00:16:20.898 --> 00:16:22.232
I don't see any buildings.

268
00:16:24.318 --> 00:16:25.484
It must be behind those hills.

269
00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:27.612
[sighs] Must it?

270
00:16:27.613 --> 00:16:29.822
- Kentaro. we agreed...
- You all agreed.

271
00:16:29.823 --> 00:16:31.616
[Lee] You got passion.
kid. I'll give you that.

272
00:16:31.617 --> 00:16:34.369
- Stop treating me like a kid.
- [Cate stammers] Hold on.

273
00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:35.996
I know what I saw.

274
00:16:35.997 --> 00:16:37.205
- [Cate] No. no. no.
- [Lee] What?

275
00:16:37.206 --> 00:16:38.290
Over there.

276
00:16:39.041 --> 00:16:41.334
- [Lee] What? Where?
- [Cate] Right there. What is that?

277
00:16:41.335 --> 00:16:42.460
[Lee] Oh. yeah. I see it.

278
00:16:42.461 --> 00:16:45.087
I don't know. Lights on an oil
rig maybe. or a local settlement.

279
00:16:45.088 --> 00:16:47.216
[Cate] Point is. it's
out there. right?

280
00:16:48.467 --> 00:16:50.635
- We follow something we can all see.
- Yeah.

281
00:16:50.636 --> 00:16:51.802
You don't know how far that is.

282
00:16:51.803 --> 00:16:54.263
That Titan can catch you
before you get halfway there.

283
00:16:54.264 --> 00:16:55.890
Whatever I saw is closer.

284
00:16:55.891 --> 00:16:58.644
- Yeah. if it exists.
- [May] Okay. Kentaro.

285
00:16:59.895 --> 00:17:04.191
Look. you have a brilliant imagination.
but now is not the time to use it.

286
00:17:05.776 --> 00:17:06.776
I'm going.

287
00:17:08.529 --> 00:17:09.862
Alone if I have to.

288
00:17:09.863 --> 00:17:12.657
Oh. my God. You
obstinate asshole.

289
00:17:13.909 --> 00:17:16.285
- So. what? You wanna die to prove a point?
- Do you?

290
00:17:16.286 --> 00:17:18.454
- No.
- [Lee] Stop. Stop. Please. stop.

291
00:17:20.123 --> 00:17:21.249
You think you saw something?

292
00:17:21.250 --> 00:17:22.375
Yeah. I know what I saw.

293
00:17:22.376 --> 00:17:26.420
Then go. and don't stop until
you find it. and then get help.

294
00:17:26.421 --> 00:17:27.506
We'll do the same.

295
00:17:29.299 --> 00:17:30.299
Good luck.

296
00:17:30.300 --> 00:17:31.844
We're all gonna need it.

297
00:17:38.225 --> 00:17:40.560
No. No. We can't
just let him leave.

298
00:17:40.561 --> 00:17:42.855
He's made his choice.
Cate. Let's go.

299
00:17:55.450 --> 00:17:58.494
[Verdugo] Dr. Barnes. I understand
you have something for us?

300
00:17:58.495 --> 00:18:00.663
[Barnes] <i>Yeah. Hold on.
Sharing my screen now.</i>

301
00:18:00.664 --> 00:18:02.290
- What are we looking at here?
- <i>Radiation.</i>

302
00:18:02.291 --> 00:18:04.375
<i>Specifically. gamma rays
in the 30 exahertz range.</i>

303
00:18:04.376 --> 00:18:07.044
- Where is this radiation coming from?
- <i>That's the crazy thing.</i>

304
00:18:07.045 --> 00:18:09.297
<i>You only see these kinds
of spikes from pulsars.</i>

305
00:18:09.298 --> 00:18:12.300
<i>Supermassive black
holes from outer space.</i>

306
00:18:12.301 --> 00:18:13.634
- But not this?
- <i>No.</i>

307
00:18:13.635 --> 00:18:15.094
<i>This was coming from the earth.</i>

308
00:18:15.095 --> 00:18:16.304
Where exactly on the earth?

309
00:18:16.305 --> 00:18:18.931
<i>Well. the detector that
picked it up is an old model.</i>

310
00:18:18.932 --> 00:18:20.016
<i>it's pretty much an antique.</i>

311
00:18:20.017 --> 00:18:22.018
- <i>They're pretty finicky.</i>
- I'll note it in the next budget request.

312
00:18:22.019 --> 00:18:23.769
- Where?
- <i>It was a rhythmic pulse.</i>

313
00:18:23.770 --> 00:18:25.521
<i>well. like... like a pulsar</i>

314
00:18:25.522 --> 00:18:28.609
<i>but as far as I know. there
aren't any pulsars in Alaska.</i>

315
00:18:30.110 --> 00:18:32.111
Thank you. Dr. Barnes.
Send us everything you have

316
00:18:32.112 --> 00:18:34.363
and we'll get an analysis
team out to you right away.

317
00:18:34.364 --> 00:18:36.240
<i>Wait. wait. wait! That's
not the big thing.</i>

318
00:18:36.241 --> 00:18:38.409
<i>The last time anyone
saw readings like this</i>

319
00:18:38.410 --> 00:18:40.537
<i>was right before the
last emergence event.</i>

320
00:18:41.121 --> 00:18:42.955
<i>From Janjira and Yucca Flats.</i>

321
00:18:42.956 --> 00:18:44.416
Before G-Day.

322
00:18:57.262 --> 00:18:58.764
[breathing heavily]

323
00:18:59.932 --> 00:19:01.974
[May. echoing] <i>Kentaro!</i>

324
00:19:01.975 --> 00:19:03.310
[Kentaro] May?

325
00:19:03.894 --> 00:19:04.895
Is that you?

326
00:19:05.979 --> 00:19:07.688
[Cate. echoing] <i>Kentaro!</i>

327
00:19:07.689 --> 00:19:08.857
Cate?

328
00:19:09.650 --> 00:19:10.651
Shaw?

329
00:19:11.902 --> 00:19:14.238
[voices whispering]

330
00:19:35.717 --> 00:19:38.177
[Cate] <i>We shouldn't
have let Kentaro go.</i>

331
00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:39.971
[grunts] He won't
survive the night.

332
00:19:39.972 --> 00:19:41.055
[sighs]

333
00:19:41.056 --> 00:19:42.765
He just needs to hang
on until we get help.

334
00:19:42.766 --> 00:19:44.977
[grunts. breathing heavily]

335
00:19:46.562 --> 00:19:49.981
- Come on. May. let me carry that bag.
- No. Stop. No!

336
00:19:49.982 --> 00:19:51.066
He wants something.

337
00:19:51.984 --> 00:19:53.193
She's getting delirious.

338
00:19:55.654 --> 00:19:57.823
Few more steps. okay?

339
00:19:58.657 --> 00:20:01.118
Think of how warm it'll
be when we get there.

340
00:20:02.703 --> 00:20:05.122
Blankets. hot coffee.

341
00:20:06.039 --> 00:20:07.623
- Whiskey.
- [chuckles]

342
00:20:07.624 --> 00:20:09.334
[breathing heavily] Come on.

343
00:20:29.229 --> 00:20:30.480
[grunts]

344
00:20:32.191 --> 00:20:33.192
No.

345
00:20:44.703 --> 00:20:46.955
[all grunting]

346
00:20:49.666 --> 00:20:52.336
[breathing heavily.
groans] Shit.

347
00:20:53.003 --> 00:20:55.881
[Cate] What? We're
back at Dad's tent?

348
00:20:58.467 --> 00:21:00.218
- How did this happen?
- [sighs]

349
00:21:00.219 --> 00:21:01.636
[Cate] We're walking in circles.

350
00:21:01.637 --> 00:21:05.598
Uh. Titans have odd effects
on their surroundings

351
00:21:05.599 --> 00:21:07.600
and how we experience them.

352
00:21:07.601 --> 00:21:12.105
The cloud we flew through. this
place. it's stranger than you think.

353
00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:14.858
It's stranger than
anybody knows.

354
00:21:16.235 --> 00:21:18.153
[shivering]

355
00:21:21.615 --> 00:21:23.866
If we don't warm her
up. she's gonna die.

356
00:21:23.867 --> 00:21:26.410
We can all die if that
Titan's still here.

357
00:21:26.411 --> 00:21:28.288
Well. I'm not leaving
here without her.

358
00:21:29.206 --> 00:21:30.874
We are not losing
another person.

359
00:21:49.142 --> 00:21:50.143
Beautiful.

360
00:22:02.155 --> 00:22:03.156
It is.

361
00:22:07.786 --> 00:22:10.956
Tell me why you don't wanna go
to your gallery opening again.

362
00:22:14.918 --> 00:22:16.670
Why does it matter
to you if I go?

363
00:22:18.630 --> 00:22:19.714
Well. it doesn't.

364
00:22:19.715 --> 00:22:23.927
But I don't think you should be
ashamed to take credit for what you do.

365
00:22:24.720 --> 00:22:25.721
What do you do?

366
00:22:30.058 --> 00:22:32.811
I just brought you here
and bared my artist's soul.

367
00:22:33.812 --> 00:22:35.855
You haven't told me
shit about yourself.

368
00:22:35.856 --> 00:22:38.274
I told you. I do computer shit.

369
00:22:38.275 --> 00:22:39.734
- Computer shit?
- Yeah.

370
00:22:39.735 --> 00:22:40.819
Yeah. okay. Come on.

371
00:22:53.999 --> 00:22:58.337
I'm from Tacoma. Tacoma
sucks. So. I came to Japan.

372
00:22:59.213 --> 00:23:00.631
Japan is cool.

373
00:23:01.507 --> 00:23:02.507
Is that better?

374
00:23:03.133 --> 00:23:04.333
[Kentaro muttering] I'm sorry.

375
00:23:04.635 --> 00:23:06.887
It's okay. You didn't
make Tacoma suck.

376
00:23:11.308 --> 00:23:14.519
So. you can stay as long as you
want. or you can come with me?

377
00:23:14.520 --> 00:23:16.771
This is your party. [sighs]

378
00:23:16.772 --> 00:23:18.732
I've already seen
all the best stuff.

379
00:23:19.483 --> 00:23:20.817
Can I see you again?

380
00:23:26.990 --> 00:23:29.033
- Give me your number. [chuckles]
- This is your phone?

381
00:23:29.034 --> 00:23:30.702
Yeah. I like a physical button.

382
00:23:34.164 --> 00:23:36.291
- [cell phone ringing]
- [Kentaro] Um. you need to...

383
00:23:37.125 --> 00:23:38.167
Ignore it.

384
00:23:38.168 --> 00:23:39.628
[buttons beeping]

385
00:23:40.838 --> 00:23:42.171
Try not to break anything.

386
00:23:42.172 --> 00:23:44.132
[chuckles] How would you tell?

387
00:23:45.425 --> 00:23:46.927
[cell phone ringing]

388
00:23:56.228 --> 00:23:57.688
Hello? Hey.

389
00:23:58.272 --> 00:24:00.315
[sighs] I'm traveling.

390
00:24:01.441 --> 00:24:02.442
For work. yeah.

391
00:24:05.362 --> 00:24:08.073
No. Look. you... you
gotta stop calling me.

392
00:24:08.574 --> 00:24:12.911
I... [sighs] I'll call
you when I'm back. yeah?

393
00:24:14.955 --> 00:24:15.956
Okay. you too.

394
00:24:17.082 --> 00:24:18.083
Yeah. bye.

395
00:24:41.106 --> 00:24:42.107
Beautiful.

396
00:24:44.651 --> 00:24:46.903
Beautiful. [shivering]

397
00:24:46.904 --> 00:24:49.489
- This shit is so beautiful.
- [Cate] May.

398
00:24:50.991 --> 00:24:53.284
Stay with me. May. May.

399
00:24:53.285 --> 00:24:56.330
Oh... [stammers] My
legs are burning.

400
00:24:57.039 --> 00:24:58.414
Like pins and needles?

401
00:24:58.415 --> 00:25:00.374
More like swords and daggers.

402
00:25:00.375 --> 00:25:02.211
- [groans]
- That's really good.

403
00:25:03.170 --> 00:25:04.629
Your nerves are waking up.

404
00:25:04.630 --> 00:25:06.005
You don't have frostbite yet.

405
00:25:06.006 --> 00:25:07.715
[May breathes shakily] Yet.

406
00:25:07.716 --> 00:25:09.091
Good bedside manner.

407
00:25:09.092 --> 00:25:10.719
[shivering]

408
00:25:12.095 --> 00:25:17.892
Hey. If anything happens to me.
just get in touch with my sister.

409
00:25:17.893 --> 00:25:20.394
Her name's... [inhales
sharply] Her name is Lyra.

410
00:25:20.395 --> 00:25:21.688
No. Let's not go there.

411
00:25:22.940 --> 00:25:25.943
She's the only... only
person that I can call.

412
00:25:27.110 --> 00:25:30.029
I'm gonna... I'm gonna
give you her number.

413
00:25:30.030 --> 00:25:31.155
I'm sure Kentaro knows h...

414
00:25:31.156 --> 00:25:33.950
No. He doesn't know shit.

415
00:25:33.951 --> 00:25:36.161
[Lee] Hope you're
not talking about me.

416
00:25:36.995 --> 00:25:39.039
[sighs] Compliments of Du-Ho.

417
00:25:40.415 --> 00:25:41.708
Crackers and chocolate.

418
00:25:42.709 --> 00:25:43.918
How's she doing?

419
00:25:43.919 --> 00:25:45.379
[breathes shakily] Better.

420
00:25:52.219 --> 00:25:53.303
[exhales sharply]

421
00:25:54.555 --> 00:25:56.807
[Lee] All right.
Her pants are dry.

422
00:26:01.019 --> 00:26:03.062
[groans] We're gonna
have to stoke that fire.

423
00:26:03.063 --> 00:26:04.272
[grunts]

424
00:26:04.273 --> 00:26:07.568
This is nothing but kindling. I
mean. it's not gonna last very long.

425
00:26:09.862 --> 00:26:11.697
And who knows what's
in your dad's papers.

426
00:26:12.364 --> 00:26:15.367
I mean. it could tell us
what he was doing here.

427
00:26:16.493 --> 00:26:19.329
Theories. discoveries.
where he went.

428
00:26:20.247 --> 00:26:21.957
[shivering]

429
00:26:25.002 --> 00:26:26.170
Let it burn.

430
00:26:26.962 --> 00:26:27.963
[breathing deeply]

431
00:26:40.517 --> 00:26:41.810
[rumbling]

432
00:26:45.022 --> 00:26:47.857
Get your gear on! We
gotta move! Come on!

433
00:26:47.858 --> 00:26:49.275
Get back to where we hid before.

434
00:26:49.276 --> 00:26:50.444
- Come on.
- May!

435
00:26:51.778 --> 00:26:54.156
- [whimpers]
- Go. go. go. go. go!

436
00:26:56.158 --> 00:26:58.318
- [whimpers] May.
- [Lee] Wait. wait. Stop. Don't move.

437
00:26:59.244 --> 00:27:01.205
[Cate] It could be
anywhere. Listen.

438
00:27:04.208 --> 00:27:05.292
[shrieks. gasps]

439
00:27:05.792 --> 00:27:07.836
[creature roars]

440
00:27:16.887 --> 00:27:18.680
I can't run from
that thing anymore.

441
00:27:23.018 --> 00:27:24.228
We may not have to.

442
00:27:24.728 --> 00:27:28.523
This morning. Outpost
47 registered readings

443
00:27:28.524 --> 00:27:31.610
I consider noteworthy.

444
00:27:32.819 --> 00:27:33.862
Dr. Barnes.

445
00:27:34.363 --> 00:27:35.821
- [tech 1] Oh. my God.
- [tech 2] What?

446
00:27:35.822 --> 00:27:38.699
That can't be right. These
readings mirror. uh...

447
00:27:38.700 --> 00:27:41.119
The gamma-ray flare before
the San Francisco...

448
00:27:42.663 --> 00:27:43.664
event.

449
00:27:44.331 --> 00:27:46.541
Call it what it was. An attack.

450
00:27:46.542 --> 00:27:48.876
Well. what do you suggest?
Full mobilization?

451
00:27:48.877 --> 00:27:51.254
- Try out your Titan warning system?
- [Tim] <i>Uh. excuse me.</i> [clears throat]

452
00:27:51.255 --> 00:27:53.673
- [Bagheri] Create a worldwide panic?
- Better than a thousand dead.

453
00:27:53.674 --> 00:27:55.466
- <i>Or 10.000.</i>
- Excuse me.

454
00:27:55.467 --> 00:27:57.802
[Bagheri] We don't know if these
creatures have malevolent intent.

455
00:27:57.803 --> 00:28:00.055
- [Tim] <i>Excuse me!</i>
- Quiet down.

456
00:28:01.431 --> 00:28:03.933
[shushes] Tim. you
have something?

457
00:28:03.934 --> 00:28:07.061
<i>We can't dismiss
Bill Randa's files.</i>

458
00:28:07.062 --> 00:28:10.356
Now. look. Lee Shaw was there.
He knows something that we don't.

459
00:28:10.357 --> 00:28:12.818
- <i>That's why he's going after the files.</i>
- Quiet!

460
00:28:14.069 --> 00:28:17.363
<i>Uh. most of you all don't
know me. and if you do.</i>

461
00:28:17.364 --> 00:28:21.869
<i>I'm the troll from the basement that
you try to avoid in the break room.</i>

462
00:28:22.578 --> 00:28:25.496
It's fine. It's not like I work here
for the after-work karaoke anyway.

463
00:28:25.497 --> 00:28:26.707
Your point.

464
00:28:27.207 --> 00:28:30.919
[sighs] <i>I thought
that we were here</i>

465
00:28:31.503 --> 00:28:35.382
<i>to learn everything we
can in any way that we can</i>

466
00:28:35.883 --> 00:28:39.428
<i>so no one else has to lose another
loved one in a Titan event.</i>

467
00:28:39.928 --> 00:28:42.555
<i>And I would've thought
that a bunch of people</i>

468
00:28:42.556 --> 00:28:47.436
<i>who signed up to study giant.
atomic-powered monsters</i>

469
00:28:47.936 --> 00:28:49.816
<i>would be a little bit
more open-minded about it.</i>

470
00:28:52.816 --> 00:28:56.236
[Lee] We may be knocked on our
asses but we're not done yet.

471
00:28:56.737 --> 00:28:58.780
'cause now we know
how our enemy works.

472
00:28:59.489 --> 00:29:00.649
- We do?
- [Shaw groans] Yeah.

473
00:29:01.116 --> 00:29:03.285
That Titan didn't go after
us. it went after the fire.

474
00:29:03.994 --> 00:29:07.497
Didn't go after Kentaro. it went
after that burning airplane engine.

475
00:29:09.082 --> 00:29:10.501
That's how it's tracking us.

476
00:29:11.043 --> 00:29:12.877
It's drawn to the
heat. Oh. my God.

477
00:29:12.878 --> 00:29:16.547
Then why did it toss that airplane
like a chew toy... [pants]

478
00:29:16.548 --> 00:29:18.133
and come chasing after us?

479
00:29:18.884 --> 00:29:22.094
Because my brother tried saving our
asses by shooting a flare at it.

480
00:29:22.095 --> 00:29:24.556
And after the flare. we
were the warmest things.

481
00:29:26.892 --> 00:29:30.479
And this is how we
beat this damn thing.

482
00:29:31.146 --> 00:29:34.857
We dangle the biggest. brightest.
hottest object we can in front of it.

483
00:29:34.858 --> 00:29:37.109
Never been so thankful
for a full bladder.

484
00:29:37.110 --> 00:29:39.153
Aviation fuel.

485
00:29:39.154 --> 00:29:40.238
Flint.

486
00:29:40.239 --> 00:29:43.699
Gonna light this thing brighter
than Times Square on VJ Day.

487
00:29:43.700 --> 00:29:45.076
Uh. what? What day?

488
00:29:45.077 --> 00:29:47.412
We build a bonfire. We feed it.

489
00:29:48.413 --> 00:29:50.831
And then while that Titan's
absorbing its heat...

490
00:29:50.832 --> 00:29:54.753
[grunts] ...we hightail it to the
coast. I'll carry you if I have to.

491
00:29:55.921 --> 00:29:57.714
[grunting]

492
00:30:15.774 --> 00:30:17.776
May. just a little
further. okay?

493
00:30:18.569 --> 00:30:19.569
We're gonna make it.

494
00:30:22.030 --> 00:30:23.156
I'm not.

495
00:30:24.741 --> 00:30:28.787
Sooner or later you're gonna
have to ditch me. okay?

496
00:30:30.873 --> 00:30:32.791
Yes. And if the time comes.

497
00:30:33.834 --> 00:30:35.335
you ditch him too.

498
00:30:36.712 --> 00:30:38.380
Save yourself. Cate.

499
00:30:39.173 --> 00:30:41.592
One of us has to make
it out of here alive.

500
00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:56.398
[voice. echoing] <i>Who's there?</i>

501
00:31:00.694 --> 00:31:01.695
Hello?

502
00:31:07.701 --> 00:31:09.995
- Hello?
- [voice. echoing] <i>What are you doing here?</i>

503
00:31:11.038 --> 00:31:12.206
Are you real?

504
00:31:13.624 --> 00:31:15.417
[voice. echoing] <i>I
thought I was alone.</i>

505
00:31:16.460 --> 00:31:17.502
So did I.

506
00:31:17.503 --> 00:31:19.063
[voice. echoing] <i>You
shouldn't be here.</i>

507
00:31:26.929 --> 00:31:28.305
[in Japanese] Dad...

508
00:31:33.852 --> 00:31:34.978
Don't leave me!

509
00:31:35.938 --> 00:31:37.189
Wait. Dad!

510
00:31:37.898 --> 00:31:38.899
It's me!

511
00:31:40.359 --> 00:31:41.360
Don't...

512
00:32:10.389 --> 00:32:12.391
[wheezing. coughing]

513
00:32:39.543 --> 00:32:40.544
[breathes shakily]

514
00:33:43.398 --> 00:33:44.482
[scratching]

515
00:33:44.483 --> 00:33:45.817
[gasps]

516
00:33:55.327 --> 00:33:56.369
[gasps]

517
00:33:56.370 --> 00:33:57.913
I did sell a few pieces...

518
00:34:01.291 --> 00:34:03.292
but Kimi dropped me anyway.

519
00:34:03.293 --> 00:34:04.628
[scratching]

520
00:34:08.841 --> 00:34:11.051
"It's a huge
opportunity." you said.

521
00:34:13.762 --> 00:34:15.097
"You're so talented."

522
00:34:16.181 --> 00:34:17.391
"You can do this."

523
00:34:18.225 --> 00:34:20.018
"I believe in you."

524
00:34:20.561 --> 00:34:22.771
That's what you said that time.

525
00:34:26.440 --> 00:34:27.440
How the hell...

526
00:34:28.150 --> 00:34:29.862
would you know if
I was ready or not?

527
00:34:30.571 --> 00:34:32.989
But I didn't want
to disappoint you.

528
00:34:33.739 --> 00:34:35.534
So I couldn't face you...

529
00:34:38.745 --> 00:34:41.748
How was I supposed to know
I'd never see you again?

530
00:34:42.416 --> 00:34:43.625
Dad?

531
00:34:48.589 --> 00:34:51.925
I wouldn't have missed
this for anything.

532
00:34:52.551 --> 00:34:54.052
Everybody loved it.

533
00:34:54.803 --> 00:34:56.262
Your mother loved it.

534
00:34:56.263 --> 00:34:57.639
[distorted] I loved it too.

535
00:34:58.682 --> 00:34:59.933
I'm proud of you.

536
00:35:01.727 --> 00:35:02.728
Congratulations.

537
00:35:03.729 --> 00:35:05.272
[distorted dialogue]

538
00:35:06.023 --> 00:35:08.025
[static]

539
00:35:49.399 --> 00:35:50.901
[static continues]

540
00:35:56.657 --> 00:35:58.408
[Cate. in English] Are
we really doing this?

541
00:35:58.909 --> 00:36:00.577
[Lee] It's a funeral pyre. Cate.

542
00:36:01.203 --> 00:36:03.955
Du-Ho always wanted to go
out in a blaze of glory.

543
00:36:03.956 --> 00:36:08.418
I'm just pouring one out for the guy
who loved getting one over on me.

544
00:36:08.961 --> 00:36:12.797
First night we met. brother.
I... I couldn't believe

545
00:36:12.798 --> 00:36:16.050
how you were drinking me
underneath the table that night.

546
00:36:16.051 --> 00:36:18.553
- [helicopter whirring]
- [Lee] And then I realized

547
00:36:18.554 --> 00:36:20.930
- every time you took a shot...
- Do you hear that?

548
00:36:20.931 --> 00:36:22.611
- Shaw. Shaw! It's...
- all you really...

549
00:36:23.433 --> 00:36:25.102
[roars]

550
00:36:26.353 --> 00:36:28.021
[both screaming]

551
00:36:30.107 --> 00:36:32.609
- Go! Run!
- May!

552
00:36:34.820 --> 00:36:37.281
Hey. big boy! Big
boy! Over here!

553
00:36:38.782 --> 00:36:41.243
Oh. Jesus. No. Where is it? No.

554
00:36:44.580 --> 00:36:46.915
- Help! Help! Help!
- [grunting]

555
00:36:48.333 --> 00:36:49.835
- [whimpering]
- [growling]

556
00:36:51.044 --> 00:36:52.462
[screaming]

557
00:36:54.131 --> 00:36:56.966
[groans] Need a shield
to ride a rocket ship.

558
00:36:56.967 --> 00:36:59.595
Dinner time. you son
of a bitch. [grunts]

559
00:37:02.222 --> 00:37:03.307
[grunts]

560
00:37:08.145 --> 00:37:09.813
[screaming]

561
00:37:11.523 --> 00:37:12.523
May. come on.

562
00:37:12.524 --> 00:37:13.734
You can do this.

563
00:37:15.319 --> 00:37:16.403
The chopper! Let's go.

564
00:37:25.412 --> 00:37:26.663
[grunting]

565
00:37:31.376 --> 00:37:33.336
[footsteps thudding]

566
00:37:33.337 --> 00:37:34.546
[roars]

567
00:37:49.228 --> 00:37:51.605
- [Cate grunting] May! Come on!
- [May] Oh. shit.

568
00:37:52.689 --> 00:37:53.815
[Cate] I got you!

569
00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:56.567
- Come on. hurry!
- [Cate] Kentaro!

570
00:37:56.568 --> 00:37:57.985
- Let's go!
- Kentaro?

571
00:37:57.986 --> 00:38:00.072
- [Kentaro] Come on. Go.
- [Lee] Go. Go.

572
00:38:02.157 --> 00:38:03.283
[Lee] Pick it up!

573
00:38:05.369 --> 00:38:07.203
[Cate shrieks]

574
00:38:07.204 --> 00:38:08.539
[grunts]

575
00:38:35.065 --> 00:38:36.399
They said the
signal was so weak.

576
00:38:36.400 --> 00:38:38.902
they almost didn't hear me
on the emergency channel.

577
00:38:41.196 --> 00:38:44.198
I never thought I'd thank someone
for abandoning their family.

578
00:38:44.199 --> 00:38:45.784
but here we are.

579
00:38:47.160 --> 00:38:49.162
Dad was there. Before me.

580
00:38:50.080 --> 00:38:52.206
- Just like at his camp.
- How do you...

581
00:38:52.207 --> 00:38:54.584
Someone had to fix the
radio that I found.

582
00:38:54.585 --> 00:38:56.253
Left a mess of shavings behind.

583
00:39:00.048 --> 00:39:01.382
He made it out.

584
00:39:01.383 --> 00:39:02.634
He's alive.

585
00:39:03.760 --> 00:39:05.137
[May] Thank you.

586
00:39:20.694 --> 00:39:22.446
[radio chatter]

587
00:39:24.948 --> 00:39:29.912
No. No. no. no. Oh. goddamn it.

588
00:39:30.579 --> 00:39:31.580
Damn it.

589
00:39:42.716 --> 00:39:43.884
[Tim] Colonel Shaw!

590
00:39:45.511 --> 00:39:47.262
It's an honor to
finally meet you!

590
00:39:48.305 --> 00:40:48.226
